question: 算定する
sourceMnemonic:
When you <kanji>calculate</kanji> and <kanji>determine</kanji> (the calculation), you are determining the calculation. That's why this word is <vocabulary>to calculate</vocabulary>.

<ja>算定する</ja> is a formal word that focuses more on the final value of a calculation, instead of the process of calculating itself.
sourceReadingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word, which usually means on'yomi readings from the kanji. If you know the readings of your kanji you'll know how to read this as well.
